{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit"]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"symbolKind":"module","roleHeading":"Framework","role":"collection","title":"SpooktacularKit","externalID":"SpooktacularKit"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"SpooktacularKit is the core library powering Spooktacular — a lightweight","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"macOS app for running macOS virtual machines. Built on Apple’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/virtualization"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"framework, it provides a Swift API for VM lifecycle management,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"IPSW installation, instant APFS cloning, and enterprise provisioning.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use SpooktacularKit directly in your Swift project, or interact with it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"through the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"text":" CLI, the Spooktacular GUI app, or the Kubernetes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"operator. All interfaces share the same library and produce identical","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"behavior.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SpooktacularKit requires an Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"running macOS 14.0 (Sonoma) or later."}]}],"name":"Important","style":"important","type":"aside"},{"level":3,"text":"Design Principles","anchor":"Design-Principles","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SpooktacularKit follows Apple’s Virtualization framework sample 